Path: This week in Nu #39
Content:
filalex added 
``--regex``
 to the 
``parse``
 command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1863] #1863
)
mhmdanas began abstracting code blocks in the book so languages could share examples (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/99] #99
)
fdnced improved the row auto-rotation heuristic (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1863] #1861
), added instructions for pipenv to nu_jupyter (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_jupyter/pull/1] #1
)
zombie110year translated the first few chapters of the book to simplified Chinese (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/97] #97
)
AaronC81 improved completions for paths with spaces (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1863] #1858
), bumped the minimum Rust version in the README (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1851] #1851
)
ryespeg finished documenting the comparisons of Nu with a set of functional and imperative languages (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/93] #93
)
jonathandturner added some notes on Nu's current progress to the README (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1854] #1854
), added string interpolation (eg ls | echo 
``{{name}} is a path``
) (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1849] #1849
), updated 
``format``
 to accept variables also (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1842] #1842
), moved error reporting from language-reporting to codespan (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1825] #1825
), fixed a bug where starship wasn't getting sent the pwd (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1822] #1822
), bumped dependencies (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1809] #1809
), moved plugins to use modern it-expansion (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1807] #1807
), added support for 
``$(block)``
 form for argument command invocation (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1801] #1801
)
JosephTLyons added a count to 
``histogram``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1853] #1853
), made 
``to json``
 pretty print indentation configurable (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1818] #1818
), added pretty printing to 
``to json``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1812] #1812
), cleaned up a blog post (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/blog/pull/23] #23
)
1ntEgr8 added a 
``--save``
 flag to 
``alias``
 to make it easier to save aliases to config (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1852] #1852
)
cjpearce fixed the missing errors for argument invocation (eg 
``$(bad command)``
 now errors correctly) (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1849] #1849
)
aeosynth changed the default history to 100k lines (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1845] #1845
)
lightclient added support for setting the max history in the config (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1837] #1837
)
thegedge removed the assuming that Value::Nothing could be used as zero (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1836] #1836
)
matsuu fixed the canonical url for the website (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/48] #48
)
Samboy218 added documentation for the 
``no_auto_pivot``
 setting (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1828] #1828
)
coolshaurya added docs for 
``shuffle``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1824] #1824
), removed the 
``-n``
 flag from 
``shuffle``
 (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1823] #1823
), fixed the 
``insert``
 command to work as documented (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1815] #1815
)
thegedge, JosephTLyons added more command examples (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1830] #1830
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1821] #1821
)
jzaefferer added docs to the 
``start``
 command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1816] #1816
)
fusepilot helped fix a typo in the contributor book (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-book/pull/25] #25
)
andrasio removed the "test-bins" feature to make it easier to run the test suite (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1820] #1820
), translated chapters of the book to Spanish (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/95] #95
)
johnterickson fixed a bug that caused 
``parse``
 to panic in some situations (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1814] #1814
)
klnusbaum added better color palette abstraction to help colors be configurable in the future (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1813] #1813
)
